{
  "message": "fuzz(jbd2-replay): 20 structured seeds across JBD2 block types and feature flags\n\nfuzz_jbd2_replay drives ffs_journal::replay_jbd2 +\nreplay_jbd2_segments against arbitrary 512-byte JBD2 journal block\nstreams and asserts (a) replay determinism, (b) result equivalence\nbetween region-based and segment-based replay, (c) ten replay-stat\ninvariants (descriptor_blocks \u2264 scanned_blocks, replayed \u2264\ndescriptor_tags, etc.). Existing 6 ad-hoc seeds covered just a few\nbasic shapes \u2014 never the JBD2 feature flag matrix or the orphaned-\ncommit / revoke paths.\n\nAdds 20 seeds covering:\n\n  Empty/garbage shapes:\n  * single all-zero 512 B block (no JBD2 magic)\n  * 4 all-zero blocks\n  * 2-byte truncated (below the 12-byte header)\n  * bad magic (JBD2_MAGIC+1) at the journal head\n\n  Superblock-only shapes (block_type 3 v1 / 4 v2):\n  * superblock_v1_only / superblock_v2_only\n  * with feature_compat=1\n  * with INCOMPAT_64BIT (0x1)\n  * with INCOMPAT_CSUM_V3 (0x10) and a non-zero UUID \u2014 drives the\n    csum_seed crc32c path\n  * with INCOMPAT_FAST_COMMIT (0x20) and num_fc_blocks=8\n  * with INCOMPAT_ASYNC_COMMIT (0x4)\n  * with max_len=0 (empty journal area)\n  * with start_block=5 (offset journal head)\n\n  Transaction sequences (block types DESCRIPTOR/COMMIT/REVOKE):\n  * superblock + descriptor + commit (minimal viable transaction)\n  * descriptor + commit with no preceding superblock\n  * two descriptors then one commit (multi-tag gather)\n  * revoke + commit (revoke-list path)\n  * orphaned commit (no preceding descriptor \u2014 must be counted in\n    stats.orphaned_commit_blocks)\n  * two transactions back-to-back (sequence 1 then 2)\n\n  Mixed sparse:\n  * superblock + 3 random blocks + commit\n\nValidated by an 11 s libFuzzer run: 146 K executions over the new\ncorpus, no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
